text: ... in the second one the protagonist starts seeing other Londoners as some of Dr. Moreau's experimental animal "Beast People" hybrids, expecting them to soon start reverting into bestiality. American (New England) versus British (Old England) attitudes to race, blood, and caste.

There is an interesting parallel between the endings of H. P. Lovecraft's "The Shadow over Innsmouth" and H. G. Wells' "The Island of Doctor Moreau" in that in the first the protagonist starts suspecting he is one of Innsmouth's inhabitants himself and has fish-frog blood, but...
